
A code made to simulate the game from the Numberphile video:
YouTube: Derangements - Numberphile
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pbXg5EI5t4c

Author: Carlos Jose Vargas Aguero
email: carlos.vargasaguero@gmail.com

The FORTRAN code generates the win ratio in a text file "wins_ratio.txt" in a log scale of range 1 to 10^5
The number of tries per game is n_tries, which is set to 10000

After the text file is generated, it is plotted with Python's Matplotlib
